The paper deals with designing a new learned index for the dictionary problem, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively discusses the use of machine learning techniques, specifically linear models, to solve the problem, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of the index for database applications, which makes cs.DB (Databases) a likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new concept of Multicriteria Data Structure, which involves optimizing the data structure based on application-specific constraints, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the proposed index, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
